text: Mahmoud Reda (; March 18, 1930 â€“ July 10, 2020) was an Egyptian dancer and choreographer. He was best known for co-founding the Reda Troupe. He was born in Cairo. The Reda brothers and Fahmy founded the state-sponsored Reda Troupe in 1959. It was made up of only twelve dancers and twelve musicians. He died on 10 July 2020, aged 90. ==References== Category:1930 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Dancers Category:Choreographers Category:People from Cairo
